text: Hot is one of the songs that got me interested in Seventeen, which led me to check out more songs, before I finally became a Carat. I love this cowboy version. I like the little changes they made in choreography here. Jeonghan had my attention the most when I'd first seen the original MV, and he continued to do so, no matter how many times I watched. But then I also noticed all the members who were fantastic. I thought of saying how The8 looked so cool, but the next moment I was in awe of Hoshi's energy, then I was like Vernon is so good, Dino is great, Joshua is amazing and I kept saying that for every member. I'm worried about Jun and Woozi's shadow dance. Jun needs to lay down... and it was on top of the sand. He slays it though. Am I worried for nothing?

Though they did the choreography under the rain and splash water for Ready to Love, but as long as the shoes were antislip, they would be fine. Is it the same though for dancing on top of the sand? Hopefully the crew and staff can prepare another legend stage again but with much more safety environment for their backdrop. 

Therefore, I really respect how professional and amazing artist every Seventeen's members are. You guys slay!
